The paper focuses on using EEG brain signals and eye movements for gender and emotion recognition, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of facial recognition technology and image processing techniques to analyze facial expressions suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of machine learning algorithms to analyze the data collected from the EEG and eye movements suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the examination of cognitive differences between males and females suggests a connection to cognitive science (cs.CY).
